content: Students must enter the college campus before 10:30 AM on working days.
All students must carry their college ID card while on campus.
Mobile phones are not allowed inside classrooms without faculty permission.
Students must maintain silence inside the library at all times.
Students must follow the appropriate college dress code while attending classes.
A minimum of 75 percent attendance is required to appear in examinations.
Students must not use unfair means during examinations.
Students must keep the campus clean and use dustbins properly.
Late submission of assignments is allowed only with valid reasons and faculty approval.
Students must follow all safety instructions while working in laboratories.
The college office is open from 10:30 AM to 5 PM on working days.
Library membership is automatically provided to all enrolled students.
Students can apply for scholarships through the Government scholarship portal.
In case of a lost ID card, students must apply for a duplicate at the Student Section.
Bonafide certificates can be requested from the Student Section and are issued within two working days.
Students must book faculty appointments at least one day in advance through the portal.
Faculty meetings are generally conducted between 10 AM and 4 PM on working days.
Emergency appointments may be allowed only with prior permission from the faculty.
If a faculty member is on leave, appointments must be rescheduled after their return.
